    "# Comparing Antenna Element Calculations with Matlab\n",

   ]

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "import scipy.io\n",

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "el = nr.AntennaElement(beamWidth=[65,65], maxAttenuation=30)\n"

    "# Depending on the input parameters the \"drawRadiation\" method can create different types of graphs. Here\n",
    "# we draw the directivity of our antenna element at the horizontal plane of zero elevation.\n",
    "radValues = el.drawRadiation(theta=90, viewAngles=(90,0), radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# We can print a selected portion of the field values returned by this function and compare the results\n",
    "# with Matlab.\n",
    "radValues.min(),radValues.max(),radValues[175:185]"

    "# Here the \"drawRadiation\" method is used to draw a 3D graph of directivity.\n",
    "radValues = el.drawRadiation(radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=True, viewAngles=(90,0))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print a selected portion of the directivity values and compare the results with Matlab. \n",
    "radValues.min(),radValues.max(),radValues[85:95,180]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f44321aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Expected (from Matlab):\n",
    "```\n",
    "array([9.75467913, 9.78024126, 9.80012292, 9.8143241 , 9.82284481,\n",
    "       9.82568505, 9.82284481, 9.8143241 , 9.80012292, 9.78024126]))\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "00d6bbb3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "# Here the \"drawRadiation\" method is used again to draw a 3D graph of directivity. This time however, we are\n",
    "# specifying the angle resolution to be 2 degree. This makes the graph generation faster but also coarser than\n",
    "# the previous one. (The default angle resolution is 1 degree)\n",
    "radValues = el.drawRadiation(theta=np.arange(0,180,2), phi=np.arange(-180,180,2), \n",
    "                             radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=True, viewAngles=(90,0))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "6e993085",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Shape of Directivity results: (180, 360)\n",
      "Maximum difference between the results: 3.552713678800501e-14\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparing the directivity calculations with Matlab\n",
    "directivity = el.getDirectivity()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read the file created by Matlab for \"directivity\" values\n",
    "directivityMatlab = scipy.io.loadmat('MatlabFiles/ElementDirectivity.mat')['directivity']\n",
    "directivityMatlab = directivityMatlab[:-1,:-1]\n",
    "assert directivityMatlab.shape==directivity.shape\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Shape of Directivity results:\", directivity.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Maximum difference between the results:\", np.abs(directivity-directivityMatlab).max())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "1b378a46",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Shape of Field values: (180, 360)\n",
      "Maximum difference between the results: 4.440892098500626e-16\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparing the field calculations with Matlab\n",
    "field = el.getField()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read the file created by Matlab for \"field\" values\n",
    "fieldMatlab = scipy.io.loadmat('MatlabFiles/ElementField.mat')['field']\n",
    "fieldMatlab = fieldMatlab[:-1,:-1]\n",
    "assert fieldMatlab.shape==field.shape\n",
    "print(\"Shape of Field values:\", field.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Maximum difference between the results:\", np.abs(field-fieldMatlab).max())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "44977e81",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Shape of power values: (180, 360)\n",
      "Maximum difference between the results: 3.197442310920451e-14\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparing the power calculations with Matlab\n",
    "powerDb = el.getPowerPatternDb()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read the file created by Matlab for \"powerDb\" values\n",
    "powerDbMatlab = scipy.io.loadmat('MatlabFiles/ElementPowerDb.mat')['powerDb']\n",
    "powerDbMatlab = powerDbMatlab[:-1,:-1]\n",
    "assert powerDbMatlab.shape==powerDb.shape\n",
    "print(\"Shape of power values:\", powerDb.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Maximum difference between the results:\", np.abs(powerDb-powerDbMatlab).max())\n"
   ]
